stylometry:
Safety stock is how much of a product you would like to have in inventory to account for the time for your order of new product to come in. If you decide for a 95% service level you have 5% in safety stock, or left over product to ensure that you are not likely to run out of that product. It is important because many times companies decide they will lose money if they run out of a product, safety stock ensures that this is not likely to occur. 

SS=MD+ZSTD

SS: Safety Stock
MD: Average 
Z: z-score of service level company wants to have
STD: Standard deviation
